Re: ProMED-mail Leprosy - India (04): (MH) 20120703.1188726
-----------------------------------------------------------
India continues to account for over 50 per cent of the global leprosy burden; however, since 2004 disease rates per 100 000 population in Brazil have exceeded those in India. [1-3] See graphs at http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/LeprosyIndia.png.

References
----------
1. Berger SA. Infectious diseases of India, 2012. 503 pages, 67 graphs, 4248 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-india/
2. Berger SA. Leprosy: global status, 2012. 236 pages, 376 graphs, 226 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/leprosy-global-status/
3. Gideon Graph Tool at http://www.GIDEONonline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Gideon-Graphs.pps

